<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,152,1260]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1197,1223]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerstmeier &amp; Eberle" authorityYear="2010" box="[604,701,1197,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Xenorthrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubris">
<emphasis box="[604,701,1197,1222]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">lugubris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a Latin adjective meaning mourning, refers to a sad looking face.
</paragraph>
